---
import { Layout } from "/layouts/layout.squirrel";
const title = "Learn"
---
<Layout>
    <h1>${title}</h1>

    Here you will learn about following:

    <ul>
        <li><b>Structure</b></li>
        <li><b>Layouts</b></li>
        <li><b>Pages</b></li>
        <li><b>Components</b></li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mt-2">Pages</h4>
    <p>A page use a layout and have components and content.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-2">Layouts</h4>
    <p>The layout define the design.</p>

    <h4 class="mt-2">Components</h4>
    <p>Components are things like a header, or a navigation bar or a breadcrumb and so on.</p>

</Layout>
